Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression with the impression of a slightly curved wooden object on one side, perpendicular to it two parallel impressions of a turned cord, about 0.2cm wide. Therefore it probably sealed a door bolt or a box. The fine brown Nile clay has inclusions of mica and was hardened after excavation without having been cleaned properly. The top is rounded and shows one scarab-like seal impressions and many finger prints around it. The seal shows a column of in hieroglyphs, at the top a very small horizontal cartouche with Mn-khpr-R', underneath 'Imn nfr nfr, underneath a curved horizontal line and an ib, rest is broken off.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
